&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Akuna:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Akuna Capital is an innovative trading firm with a strong focus on collaboration, cutting-edge technology, data driven solutions and automation. We specialize in providing liquidity as an options market-maker ‚Äì meaning we are committed to providing competitive quotes that we are willing to both buy and sell. To do this successfully we design and implement our own low latency technologies, trading strategies and mathematical models.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Founding Partners, Andrew Killion and Mitchell Skinner, first conceptualized Akuna in their hometown of Sydney. They opened the firm‚Äôs first office in 2011 in the heart of the derivatives industry and the options capital of the world ‚Äì Chicago. Today, Akuna is proud to operate from additional offices in Sydney, Shanghai, and Boston.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Akuna Hong Kong opened in mid-2018 and will aim to replicate the success of the Chicago office in providing competitive market making services on listed derivatives on the HKEx. Akuna Hong Kong will work closely with all Akuna offices, but particularly with our Shanghai and Sydney teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you‚Äôll do as a Responsible Officer at Akuna:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Akuna is looking for a Responsible Officer to join our growing team. This individual will work closely with all aspects of the business, including Trading, Compliance, Risk and Finance, to ensure Akuna is meeting its regulatory requirements. Well qualified candidates will demonstrate a strong understanding of SFO regulations and guidelines, have prior experience supervising daily market making operations, and possess the ability to effectively communicate with both regulatory bodies and cross-functional teams within Akuna. In this role, you will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee and supervise SFC Type 1 and Type 2 daily operations, specifically market making operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage communications with SFC, HKEx and other regulatory bodies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the company meets full regulatory compliance with SFO and other statutory regulations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with senior management to help review business operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Formulate, review and update operational procedures to ensure full regulatory compliance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
